---
import '../assets/css/use-cases.css';

import {
  LOG_SEARCH,
  APP_SEARCH,
  EDGE_SEARCH
} from '../assets/images';

import DefaultLayout from '../layouts/DefaultLayout.astro';
import Subscription from '../components/Subscription.astro';
import HeaderTitle from '../components/HeaderTitle.astro';
---

<DefaultLayout>
  <main id="use-cases">
    <!-- Header -->
    <HeaderTitle title={'Use Cases'} />

    <!-- Use-cases -->
    <div class="use-cases-section mt-100 mb-100">
      <div class="container flex-direction-column">
        <div class="row w-100 align-item-center justify-content-between">
          <div class="text-contain col-6" scrolls-duration="1500">
            <h1>Log Search</h1>
            <p>Searching for logs for your applications can be tedious and challenging. ZincSearch solves the
              problem very elegantly. You can use standard log forwarders like fluent, fluent-bit,
              vector, syslog-ng, or others to forward logs to ZincSearch. ZincSearch can then store the indexed logs in
              S3 or on disk and provide fast search for your logs.</p>
            <p>Log forwarders can read the log files incrementally as new logs appear in them and then
              forward them in batches to be more efficient in sending them.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-6" scrolls-duration="2000">
            <img src={LOG_SEARCH} alt="log-search-img" title="log-search-img"
              class="fluid-img">
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr>
        <div class="row w-100 align-item-center justify-content-between">
          <div class="text-contain col-6 right" scrolls-duration="1500">
            <h1>App Search</h1>
            <p>Almost every application requires search functionality. For example, if you are using a relational database for your
              application needs, using SQL LIKE for text searches has the potential to kill the database. ZincSearch
              is the perfect solution to provide search on these low-powered devices.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-6 left" scrolls-duration="2000">
            <img src={APP_SEARCH} alt="app-search" title="app-search"
              class="fluid-img">
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr>
        <div class="row w-100 align-item-center justify-content-between">
          <div class="text-contain col-6" scrolls-duration="1500">
            <h1>Edge Search</h1>
            <p>You have low powered devices on the edge that require search functionality.
              ZincSearch is the perfect solution to provide search on these low powered devices.</p>
            <p>e.g. Your IoT/IDS/IPS/Firewall device needs search capability so users can search for
              required data or logs.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-6" scrolls-duration="2000">
            <img src={EDGE_SEARCH} alt="edge-search" title="edge-search"
              class="fluid-img">
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <Subscription />
  </main>
</DefaultLayout>